<font color="#FF0000">SEEING BOTH SIDES</font><br>
<tt>Tue Nov 11 12:01:16 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Today, like those who favor strong legs and fast horses, I will drift back into the days of my youth and ignorance.<br>
With slack jaw I will gaze at my Grandfather and Uncles..my <br>
Sainted Father.. all who walked off the battle fields of yesterday.  I will remember the awe and the mystery of what it was all about.<br><br>
I will return to the horrors of Vietnam to visit with long lost friends..to laugh and to cry..to do and to die..and ultimately to stand here in pain and struggle..to reason why.<br><br>
I will stand among the young..an old Dog Soldier and fill the eyes of the innocent.  Like my fathers before me I will not be able to answer their silent questions, but perhaps fan the flames of patriotism in their small hearts.  Other surviving veterans will stand with me, coming to stand where my missing friends would have stood...and we shall rejoice and lament together.<br><br>
I will feel lost and confused.  My thoughts will drift and I will ask &quot;Why&quot; over and over.  When the Colors pass in front of me and my daughter takes my hand..I will find the answer!<br><br>
God Bless You on this Sacred Day<br>
Mustang Two Four
